# AGENTS.md

## Scope

This is the global agent instruction index for this machine.

Use `~/.agents/` as the canonical folder for agent configuration. Runtime-specific paths such as `~/.claude/` are compatibility aliases, not separate sources of truth.

## Directory Roles

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `~/.agents/AGENTS.md` | Global instruction index |
| `~/.agents/instructions/` | Operating rules loaded when relevant |
| `~/.agents/references/` | Tool and domain references |
| `~/.agents/memory/` | Trigger-loaded context |
| `~/.agents/skills/` | Installed skills |
| `~/.agents/plugins/` | Plugin and marketplace state |
| `~/.agents/state.json` | Setup state |

Do not put global workflow rules in `memory/`. Do not put remembered facts or historical notes in `instructions/`.

## Memory

Memory is trigger-loaded context. It is split by function:

| Folder | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `memory/preferences/` | User behavior, voice, learned patterns, and modeling context |
| `memory/reference/` | Lookup facts and directories |
| `memory/records/` | Append-only logs, health reports, decisions, and message records |

Load memory only when the task calls for it.

## Compatibility Links

Expected Claude compatibility links:

```text
~/.claude/CLAUDE.md -> ~/.agents/AGENTS.md
~/.claude/memory -> ~/.agents/memory
~/.claude/skills -> ~/.agents/skills
```

Keep Dex setup narrow: bootstrap the current topology, verify links, and report drift. Do not personalize the user's memory or migrate old vault files unless explicitly requested.
